# Add Error Handling and Logging

Enhance error handling and add logging to existing code following best practices.

## Logging Requirements
1. Inject `ILogger<T>` via constructor
2. Log at appropriate levels (Information, Warning, Error)
3. Include relevant context in log messages
4. Never log sensitive data (file contents, personal info)
5. Use structured logging with message templates

## Error Handling Requirements
1. Validate inputs before processing
2. Return appropriate HTTP status codes
3. Catch exceptions from external libraries
4. Provide descriptive error messages
5. Hide sensitive stack traces in production

## Service with Logging Template
```csharp
namespace CV_extractor;

public interface IServiceWithLogging
{
    (Result? result, string? error, int statusCode) ProcessData(InputData input);
}

public class ServiceWithLogging : IServiceWithLogging
{
    private readonly ILogger<ServiceWithLogging> _logger;
    
    public ServiceWithLogging(ILogger<ServiceWithLogging> logger)
    {
        _logger = logger;
    }
    
    public (Result? result, string? error, int statusCode) ProcessData(InputData input)
    {
        _logger.LogInformation("Processing data started");
        
        // Validation
        if (!IsValidInput(input))
        {
            _logger.LogWarning("Invalid input received: {ValidationError}", "Input is null or empty");
            return (null, "Invalid input", StatusCodes.Status400BadRequest);
        }
        
        // Processing with error handling
        try
        {
            var result = PerformProcessing(input);
            _logger.LogInformation("Processing completed successfully. Result count: {Count}", result.Count);
            return (result, null, StatusCodes.Status200OK);
        }
        catch (ExternalLibraryException ex)
        {
            _logger.LogError(ex, "External library failed during processing: {ErrorMessage}", ex.Message);
            return (null, $"Processing failed: {ex.Message}", StatusCodes.Status500InternalServerError);
        }
        catch (Exception ex)
        {
            _logger.LogError(ex, "Unexpected error during processing");
            return (null, "An unexpected error occurred", StatusCodes.Status500InternalServerError);
        }
    }
    
    private static bool IsValidInput(InputData input)
    {
        return input != null && !string.IsNullOrWhiteSpace(input.Value);
    }
    
    private static Result PerformProcessing(InputData input)
    {
        // Processing logic
        return new Result();
    }
}
```

## Enhanced SkillExtractorService with Logging
```csharp
public class SkillExtractorService : ISkillExtractorService
{
    private readonly ILogger<SkillExtractorService> _logger;
    
    public SkillExtractorService(ILogger<SkillExtractorService> logger)
    {
        _logger = logger;
    }
    
    public (List<string> skills, string? error, int statusCode) ExtractSkillsFromPdf(IFormFile file)
    {
        _logger.LogInformation("Starting skill extraction from PDF: {FileName}", file?.FileName ?? "null");
        
        if (!IsValidPdfFile(file))
        {
            var error = GetFileValidationError(file);
            _logger.LogWarning("File validation failed: {Error}", error);
            return (new List<string>(), error, StatusCodes.Status400BadRequest);
        }
        
        string extractedText;
        try
        {
            extractedText = ExtractTextFromPdf(file);
            _logger.LogInformation("Successfully extracted text from PDF. Length: {Length}", extractedText.Length);
        }
        catch (Exception ex)
        {
            _logger.LogError(ex, "Failed to parse PDF file: {FileName}", file.FileName);
            return (new List<string>(), $"Failed to parse PDF file. {ex.Message}", StatusCodes.Status500InternalServerError);
        }
        
        var skillsSection = GetSkillsSection(extractedText);
        
        if (string.IsNullOrWhiteSpace(skillsSection))
        {
            _logger.LogWarning("Skills section not found in PDF: {FileName}", file.FileName);
            return (new List<string>(), "Skills section not found.", StatusCodes.Status200OK);
        }
        
        var skills = ParseSkills(skillsSection);
        _logger.LogInformation("Successfully extracted {Count} unique skills from PDF: {FileName}", 
            skills.Count, file.FileName);
        
        return (skills, null, StatusCodes.Status200OK);
    }
    
    // ... rest of the methods
}
```

## Logging Levels Guide

### LogInformation
- Normal flow of application
- Successful operations
- Important milestones
```csharp
_logger.LogInformation("Processing started for file: {FileName}", fileName);
_logger.LogInformation("Found {Count} skills in PDF", skillCount);
```

### LogWarning
- Unusual situations that are not errors
- Missing optional data
- Recoverable issues
```csharp
_logger.LogWarning("Skills section not found in file: {FileName}", fileName);
_logger.LogWarning("File size exceeds recommended limit: {Size} bytes", fileSize);
```

### LogError
- Exceptions and failures
- Operations that failed
- Include exception object for stack trace
```csharp
_logger.LogError(ex, "Failed to parse PDF: {FileName}", fileName);
_logger.LogError("Unexpected error during processing: {ErrorMessage}", ex.Message);
```

### LogDebug (Development only)
- Detailed diagnostic information
- Variable values during debugging
```csharp
_logger.LogDebug("Regex pattern matched at index: {Index}", matchIndex);
_logger.LogDebug("Extracted text preview: {Preview}", textPreview);
```

## Structured Logging Best Practices
```csharp
// ? Good: Use message templates with named parameters
_logger.LogInformation("Processing file {FileName} with size {FileSize} bytes", fileName, fileSize);

// ? Bad: String interpolation (not structured)
_logger.LogInformation($"Processing file {fileName} with size {fileSize} bytes");

// ? Good: Include relevant context
_logger.LogError(ex, "Failed to extract skills from {FileName}. File size: {FileSize}", fileName, fileSize);

// ? Bad: Generic messages without context
_logger.LogError(ex, "An error occurred");
```

## Error Response Patterns

### Client Errors (400-level)
```csharp
// Bad Request (400)
if (file == null)
    return TypedResults.BadRequest(new { error = "File is required" });

// Not Found (404)
if (resource == null)
    return TypedResults.NotFound(new { error = "Resource not found" });

// Unprocessable Entity (422)
if (!IsValidFormat(data))
    return TypedResults.UnprocessableEntity(new { error = "Invalid data format" });
```

### Server Errors (500-level)
```csharp
// Internal Server Error (500)
try
{
    var result = await ProcessAsync();
}
catch (Exception ex)
{
    _logger.LogError(ex, "Processing failed");
    return TypedResults.Problem(
        detail: "An error occurred while processing your request",
        statusCode: StatusCodes.Status500InternalServerError
    );
}
```

## Exception Handling Patterns

### Specific Exception Types
```csharp
try
{
    return ProcessPdf(file);
}
catch (PdfException ex)
{
    _logger.LogError(ex, "PDF parsing failed: {FileName}", file.FileName);
    return (null, "Invalid PDF file format", 400);
}
catch (IOException ex)
{
    _logger.LogError(ex, "File I/O error: {FileName}", file.FileName);
    return (null, "Unable to read file", 500);
}
catch (Exception ex)
{
    _logger.LogError(ex, "Unexpected error processing file: {FileName}", file.FileName);
    return (null, "An unexpected error occurred", 500);
}
```

### Using Finally for Cleanup
```csharp
Stream? stream = null;
try
{
    stream = file.OpenReadStream();
    return ProcessStream(stream);
}
catch (Exception ex)
{
    _logger.LogError(ex, "Processing failed");
    throw;
}
finally
{
    stream?.Dispose();
    _logger.LogDebug("Resources cleaned up");
}
```

## Configuration for Logging (appsettings.json)
```json
{
  "Logging": {
    "LogLevel": {
      "Default": "Information",
      "Microsoft.AspNetCore": "Warning",
      "CV_extractor": "Debug"
    }
  }
}
```

## Anti-Patterns to Avoid
```csharp
// ? Don't swallow exceptions silently
try { Process(); } catch { }

// ? Don't log and rethrow
try { Process(); }
catch (Exception ex)
{
    _logger.LogError(ex, "Error");
    throw; // This will duplicate the error in logs
}

// ? Don't expose stack traces to clients in production
catch (Exception ex)
{
    return BadRequest(ex.ToString()); // Security risk!
}

// ? Don't log sensitive data
_logger.LogInformation("Processing CV with content: {Content}", pdfContent);

// ? Do log safe metadata
_logger.LogInformation("Processing CV with length: {Length} characters", pdfContent.Length);
```

## Checklist
- [ ] ILogger<T> injected via constructor
- [ ] Logging at appropriate levels (Info, Warning, Error)
- [ ] Structured logging with message templates
- [ ] Exception objects included in error logs
- [ ] No sensitive data in logs
- [ ] Appropriate HTTP status codes returned
- [ ] Descriptive error messages for clients
- [ ] Exception types handled specifically where possible
- [ ] Resources cleaned up in finally blocks or using statements
